HEADWORD: Enwomb
<hw>En*womb"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Enwombed</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Enwombing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To
conceive in the womb.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To bury, as it were in a womb; to hide, as in a
gulf, pit, or cavern.</def> <rj><au>Donne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

